            "text": "General Motors doesn’t seem too keen on the Chevy Camaro in general these days. Not only has it been trailing the Ford Mustang and Dodge Challenger in sales for some time, GM pulled the plug on production repeatedly in 2021, thanks to the chip shortage. What’s more, we learned there definitely won’t be a 6th-gen Z/28, a fact which has angered the faithful.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
